    "sessionOverview": "This session introduces the fundamental concept of 'Life Processes' for Class X students. It defines life processes as essential functions that maintain living organisms. The lesson focuses on two critical initial processes: Nutrition (autotrophic vs. heterotrophic) and Respiration (aerobic vs. anaerobic), establishing a foundation for understanding how energy is obtained and utilized.",
