        "conceptName": "Life Processes",
        "definition": "Essential biological functions that maintain the life of an organism.",
        "coreExplanation": "Without these processes, organisms cannot survive. They include getting food (nutrition), breaking it down for energy (respiration), moving nutrients around (transportation), and removing waste (excretion).",
