        "definition": "Respiration with oxygen (aerobic) releases more energy than respiration without oxygen (anaerobic).",
        "coreExplanation": "In aerobic respiration, glucose is completely broken down into CO2 and water. In anaerobic, it breaks partially into lactic acid or alcohol/CO2.",
        "importance": "Explains muscle fatigue and industrial uses of fermentation.",
        "observedIn": [
          "Heavy exercise",
          "Bread making"
        ],
        "whyStudyIt": "To understand energy efficiency in different organisms.",
        "relationshipWithPrevious": "Connects to nutrition (glucose source).",
