      "Autotrophs make their own food; Heterotrophs depend on others.",
      "Photosynthesis is the process by which plants convert light to chemical energy.",
      "Aerobic respiration requires oxygen and yields high energy.",
      "Anaerobic respiration occurs without oxygen, yielding less energy."
    ],
    "detailedContent": "Life processes are continuous activities that keep an organism alive. The first step is Nutrition. Organisms are either Autotrophs (like green plants) which synthesize their own food using sunlight and chlorophyll, or Heterotrophs (like animals and fungi) which consume other organisms for energy. Once food is obtained, it must be broken down to release energy through Respiration. This can happen in two ways: Aerobic respiration uses oxygen to completely break down glucose into carbon dioxide and water, releasing a large amount of energy. Anaerobic respiration occurs without oxygen (e.g., in yeast or muscle cells during heavy exercise), resulting in incomplete breakdown products like lactic acid or alcohol and less energy."
